iSide note: I generated that chart with an awesome command-line	
iplotter called jp [0]. My tracker (which needs a lot of coded	
icleanup) can be found here [1].	
i	
h[0] jp	URL:http://github.com/sgreben/jp
h[1] track	URL:http://github.com/jamestomasino/dotfiles/blob/master/bash/.functions/track
i	
iThe final command to generate that chart:	
i	
i  # my csv is formatted (year,month,day,weight)	
i  awk -F "," '{print $1 "-" $2 "-" $3 "," $4}' weight.csv | \	
i    jp \	
i      -input csv \	
i      -xy '[*][0,1]' \	
i      -canvas braille \	
i      -height 25 \	
i      -width 67	
